  "title": "Complexity as Variable",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "33743da43358c1f2",
      "text": "If you think of [[Complexity]] as an incremental [[Variable]] (Steigerungsvariable) – and this is precisely why [[Niklas Luhmann]] is combining the rationality discussion and the complexity discussion – then you can imagine that a system with, let's say, tested rationality and tested complexity operates differently and is organized differently than simpler systems that do not have this evolution or this planning behind them. That is, one can imagine that among the complexity patterns – you remember that these are always selection patterns – there are those that are better suited to making irritations from the environment processable in the system."
    },
